<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2346] mvn bundle:clean removes all, even the existing resources</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2346</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When launching mvn bundle:clean, my local repository.xml file is fully emptied. However, it contained some valid resources. When debugging I can see that the computed file URL are wrong:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At line 149 -&amp;gt;  File file = new File( localRepoPath, value );&lt;br/&gt;
The File constructor expects a pathname when the variable &apos;value&apos; is an URI. So the expression file.exists() always returns false.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
